OL,6,GEvery journalist knows how Sunday
OL,7,Gshifts can be dull.
OL,9,FThere might be nothing in the diary
OL,10,Fand no major events to report.
OL,12,FThe cynical hacks who give the
OL,13,Fprofession a bad name may even find
OL,14,Fthemselves hoping for a serious
OL,15,Faccident, fire or crime.
OL,17,FLuckily that degree of cynicism is not
OL,18,Fusually found amongst broadcast
OL,19,Fjournalists.
OL,21,FStill Sundays can be quiet days in
OL,22,Fregional newsrooms.
